### Session 19 (Apr 5)
- **Topic**: Canvas mode broken on Vercel -- ng-content content projection bug
- **What happened**:
  1. Diagnosed root cause: `DashboardShellComponent` had two `<ng-content />` slots in `@if (isCanvas())`/`@else` branches. Angular's content projection can't handle this -- projected `<router-outlet />` from `DashboardLayoutComponent` was silently discarded.
  2. Bug was introduced in commit `a681948` (PR #56, Apr 3) which converted `<router-outlet />` to `<ng-content />` for content projection architecture. The conversion maintained the two-branch pattern that worked with `<router-outlet />` but is fatal for `<ng-content />`.
  3. Fix: moved the single `<ng-content />` outside all `@if`/`@else` blocks. Content wrapper uses CSS class bindings (`canvas-content` vs `shell-content-desktop`) to switch styling. `canvas-host` became `position: fixed` (no layout impact). Host element now handles panning mousedown.
  4. Added 4 new static regression tests in `tests/static/dashboard-shell.spec.ts`: "has exactly ONE ng-content", "ng-content is NOT inside an @if or @else block", "uses canvas-content class", "uses shell-content-desktop class".
  5. Added section 29 to `dashboard-layout-lessons` SKILL.md documenting the rule and root cause.
  6. Added entry to Known Fragile Areas table in longterm-memory.mdc.
  7. All 36 shell static tests pass. All lint + type-check pass. Build clean.
  8. Pushed fix to `dev` (commit `647223a`). Vercel preview will auto-deploy.

